Today it hit me, like a brick. Of all the time we‚Äôve spent here in my home land, it hit me the most today. As I walked through the cemetery, full of those who used to breathe life into this land, how is it that we honour them? Those who came before us, the  inheritance they‚Äôve left for us, the life they‚Äôve built as our foundation, the traditions they‚Äôve kept so that we may have a place to belong to. And today, more than ever, I‚Äôm determined to continue this journey to find out who I am because of them. Don‚Äôt forget your elders. And if you don‚Äôt know who they are yet, then seek them. Find out. üèî
Thank you @taylorwitiw for being with me through this journey and putting up with my endless crying. .
